'''Sonia Shirsat''' (सोनिया शिरसाट, b. 1980, Ponda) ek [[Bharot]]antli [[Fado]] gavpi. Ti [[Goen]]chi, jem 1961 vorsa meren ek [[Purtugez]] vosahot asli ani atam [[Bharot]]achem ek [[Rajio]] zavn asa. Tika "Jogantli [[Goen]]chea songitachi Rajdut".<ref name="DaijiWorld">{{cite web|title=Doha: Music, football to blend at World Goa Day celebrations|url=http://www.daijiworld.com/news/news_disp.asp?n_id=199265|publisher=Daijiworld|date=4 November 2013|access-date=13 September 2016}}</ref> mhonn pachartat ani tinnem sonvsar bhor, [[Bharot]]ant ani chodd korun [[Goean]]tlea sonskrutik ani songitachea suvalleamni kariokrom keleat. Ti 13 vegllea bhasamni gaita<ref name="GoaStreets">{{cite web|last1=Abreu|first1=Aliya|title=Thank You For The Music, Sonia Shirsat|url=http://goastreets.com/thank-you-for-the-music-sonia-shirsat/|publisher=Goa Streets|date=20 November 2015|access-date=13 September 2016}}</ref>

== Fattbhuim ==
Survatek, Shirsat kaideant ek veakhean divpi asli. [[Goean]]tlea vortomonpotrache niall hannim nond kelam ki tinnem "ulovpache kosbent, ti vevsaik gavpi zavche poilim ek ontoraxttrio tosrip pottkailam,".<ref name="ToI">{{cite web|last1=Rodrigues|first1=Jonathan|title=A little bit of Portugal in PONDA|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/goa/A-little-bit-of-Portugal-in-PONDA/articleshow/46006487.cms|work=The Times of India|date=25 January 2015|access-date=13 September 2016}}</ref> Tinnem LL.M (Master's in Law) podvi melloilea.<ref name="ToI" /> Ti Ti chhond koxi gavpak lagli ani ti ek vevsaik gavpi 1999 vorsa pasun asa.<ref name="ToI" /> Tichi avoi Romi Katolk ani ticho bapui, Hindu.<ref name="ToI" />

== Fado-nt proves ==
Shirsat, [[Bharot]]eam thoddea modem, ekuch nhoi zalear, [[Fado]]-nt  utkruxtt, ek songitachi tora zacho sod [[Purtugal]]ant 1820 vo adim sumarak asa; ektti zavn asa. Tika thoddim vorsam  fattim Goeant gitar xikoitalo, tea [[Purtugez]] [[gitarist]] Antonio Chainho haka xroi dita. Kariaxalla zalea uprant, to Fado gavpachea sodant aslo. Shirsat-icho tallo "hea kantarak poripurnnant boslo", ani hea vorvim “ticho sumell hea torant” zalo, oxem ti sangta. Panch vorsam modekat, tinnem apli poili ekoddi kariavoll 2008 vorsa [[Purtugal]]ant keli.

2016 meren, tinnem [[Goem]], [[Damanv]], [[Bangalore]], [[Mumboi]], [[Delhi]], [[Kolkata]], [[Luxembourg]], [[Macau]], [[Kuwait]], [[France]], [[Singapore]], [[Hawaii]], [[Nepal]], [[Canada]], [[London]], [[Dubai]], [[Muscat]], [[Lisbon]] ani [[Qatar]] hanga kariakrom keleat.<ref name="DaijiWorld" /> Tinnem [[California]],  [[Toronto]],  [[Paris]],  [[Porto]],  [[Oeiras]] ani [[Seoul]] hangai kariavolli keleat.

Shirsat hinnem nanvvostea jogantlea [[Fado]] gavpeam sangata dakhovnneo keleat, zantunt Katia Guerreiro, Maria Ana Bobone, Raquel Tavares, Rao Kyao, Carlos do Carmo, Argentina Santos, Miguel Capucho, Ricardo Rocha ani Mestro Antonio Chainho hancho somavex asa.<ref name="BlueFrog">{{cite web|title=Sonia Shirsat|url=http://www.bluefrog.co.in/sonia-shirsat|work=BlueFrog|publisher=Blue Frog Media|access-date=13 September 2016}}</ref> Tinnem sabar favtti zaiteach [[Purtugal]]ant aslolea TV vahinicher kariavolli keleat, zantunt jivea dakhovnneacho somavex asa ani hem [[RTPI]], Sociedade Independente de Comunicação andi Televisão Independente hantunt zavnk pavlam.<ref name="BlueFrog" />

Goeant, tika sabar kodden jivea kariavollim khatir vollkhotat zantuntCalangute-chea Art Chamber<ref>{{cite web|last1=Sudan|first1=Jugneeta|title=Alchemical Music|url=http://www.navhindtimes.in/alchemical-music/|work=The Navhind Times|date=28 August 2016|access-date=13 September 2016}}</ref> hacho somavex asat .

== Her prapteo ==
Shirsat hi ekuch vevsaik Fadista (Fado gavpi) Bharoti Upkhonddant asa, ek tora tinnem 2003 vorsa savn apnnailea. Ti kariaxallo hatalltta ani nim-xastrio torachea songit Fado hacher ulovpam korta. Purtugez Fado xivai, Shirsat-ak Paromporik ani Pop songit Goeant gavpi mhonn vollkhotat.

== Songitxastr ani dakhovnneo ==

* Agost 2016: Fado in the City dakhovnn
* 2013: Ek Konkani album Ugddas, uzvaddailo ji ek lokprio kantaranchi punji tea bhaxechi zavn asa.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Achrekar|first1=Pratima|title=It's all about memories: Sonia Shirsat|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/music/news/Its-all-about-memories-Sonia-Shirsat/articleshow/18710513.cms|work=The Times of India|date=27 February 2013|access-date=13 September 2016}}</ref> He punjent famad songitkaranchea songitacho torzumo zoxe porim Alfred Rose, Chris Perry, Frank Fernand, Wilfy Remembus, heram sangata asa. Shirsat orxim Fado gavpa khatir gazlea, zorui ti Konknni songita khatirui halim vavurta.
* Mas 2010: 'Lisgoa' albumachem vimochon zantunt Shirsat hinnem Antonio Chainho sangata kam kelam. 
* Mai 2010: Shirsat hinnem aplo poilo album, 'Saudades de Fado', Rock ani Raaga,hanchea sangata Goeant uzvaddaila.
* 2006: Purtugalant  Fado xixvruti khatir venchpant aili.<ref name="GoaStreets" />

== Tosripam ==
Shirsat hinnem 2016 Abrilant: Boreantli Gavpi (Ostori) Tosrip<ref>{{cite web|title=TAG awards the cream of the Konkani music and song world|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/goa/TAG-awards-the-cream-of-the-Konkani-music-and-song-world/articleshow/51644391.cms|work=The Times of India|date=1 April 2016|access-date=13 September 2016}}</ref>  Tiatr Academy of Goa koddlean melloilam.

Tika Ustad Bismilla Khan Yuva Puroskar, 2016, Paromporik Songit<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://sangeetnatak.gov.in/uploads/2017-18/PressReleaseUBYP2016.pdf|title=Sangeet Natak Akademi|last=|first=|date=26 May 2017|work=Sangeet Natak Akademi|access-date=18 October 2018}}</ref> hea vorgonnant mell’lla zo Sangeet Natak Akademi, Bharotachea Sorkarachea Sonskrut Montrailoen bhettoila. Yuva Srujan Puroskar 2011, Goenchea Sorkaran Tornnatteanchea vorgonnant soglleant vhodd tosrip sonskrutaie vibhagant  tika divpant aila.

== Prosar madheomachi protikria ==
''The Hindu '' vortomanpotran tiche vixim oxem mhollam: "Sonia ek chomotkari gavpi jika ek bhovgunni tallo asa. Boreantli bori Bharotantli Fadista sogllea kallant asun, hea fixalkaiechea gavpean jog bhor bhonvddi marlea."<ref>{{cite web|last1=Moses R.|first1=Allan|title=From coast to coast|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/from-coast-to-coast/article784325.ece|work=The Hindu|date=27 March 2010|access-date=13 September 2016}}</ref>

